<div class="mdui-typo"><h1 id="pleasant-adj">pleasant <strong><em>adj</em></strong></h1>
<p>英 /'pleznt/    美 /'pleznt/  </p>
<h2 id="_1">释义</h2>
<h4 id="1-nice">1.★ <strong>令人愉快的；舒适的 (nice)；礼貌而友善的：</strong></h4>
<p>反 unpleasant </p>
<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>I hope you’ll have a pleasant journey.
祝你 (们) 旅途愉快！</p><footer>人教① – 3</footer></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p><strong>It was pleasant to</strong> sit in a sidewalk cafe and watch people pass. 
坐在路边咖啡馆看着人来人往真是惬意。</p></div>

<div class="mdui-typo"><blockquote><p>He had a pleasant manner and was a gifted public speaker.
他态度和蔼，是一个有天赋的演说家。</p><footer>2010 广东</footer></div>

<h2 id="_2">派生词汇</h2>
<p>pleasantly /'plezntli/ adv   </p></div>